
/*
 * The code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes to a specific location in the node hierarchy. It adds nodes retrieved by [get-nodes] from [.arguments] to the [where] clause of a [data.read] operation. 
 * 
 * 1. [add] - Appends nodes to the specified location in the node hierarchy.
 * 2. [get-nodes] - Retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node set.
 */
add:x:./*/data.read/*/where/*
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*
